    <p>• Only Sul­tan Ab­dul­lah, 61, can re­solve the grow­ing po­lit­i­cal im­passe. While his role is largely cer­e­mo­nial, the monarch has the sole power to ap­point the prime min­is­ter whom he be­lieves en­joys the ma­jor­ity sup­port of the elected rep­re­sen­ta­tives in Par­lia­ment. If that is not vi­able, he can also – on the ad­vice of the prime min­is­ter – dis­solve Par­lia­ment, af­ter which an elec­tion has to be held within 60 days.</p>

